Because my stated priorities put harmony‑first pop and concise, singable, well‑sequenced tracks front and center (while also demanding warm analogue mastering, natural dynamics and minimal glossy artifice), the Original single‑session AOR remaster aligns more closely overall. It delivers the multitracked vocal harmonies, short focused solos, punchy analogue dynamics and lack of overcompression I prize. I therefore reject the expansive double‑LP not because it’s sonically poor — it meets my warm/mastering and dynamic ideals — but because its extended, improvisatory, side‑long focus is less compatible with my primary desire for concise, melody‑led, harmony‑rich songs and sing‑along choruses.

